WEBVTT

00:00:01.451 --> 00:00:04.454 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Welcome to JW Broadcasting®!

00:00:04.454 --> 00:00:06.790 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What do we have in store for you?

00:00:06.790 --> 00:00:08.792 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here are some highlights.

00:00:08.792 --> 00:00:12.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
DiDi Brown lost her daughter
in an unimaginable tragedy.

00:00:13.997 --> 00:00:16.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How did Jehovah comfort her?

00:00:16.599 --> 00:00:19.903 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Racial and national prejudice
is hard to overcome for some people.

00:00:20.737 --> 00:00:25.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’ll go to Greece
and see a beautiful example

00:00:25.141 --> 00:00:27.277 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of impartial love in action.

00:00:27.277 --> 00:00:29.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And our new song reminds us

00:00:29.279 --> 00:00:31.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that when we make time for Jehovah,

00:00:31.414 --> 00:00:34.884 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we feel his presence in our life.

00:00:34.884 --> 00:00:39.456 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is JW Broadcasting for March 2022.

00:00:59.275 --> 00:01:01.277 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is no doubt that we’re living

00:01:01.277 --> 00:01:05.148 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
in “critical times hard to deal with,”

00:01:05.148 --> 00:01:07.717 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
just as the apostle Paul prophesied

00:01:07.717 --> 00:01:11.755 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
under inspiration in 2 Timothy chapter 3.

00:01:12.789 --> 00:01:16.726 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many times, we’ve read Matthew chapter 24,

00:01:16.726 --> 00:01:19.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Mark chapter 13, Luke chapter 21,

00:01:19.996 --> 00:01:23.099 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Revelation chapter 6.

00:01:23.099 --> 00:01:25.802 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But who would ever have known

00:01:25.802 --> 00:01:28.838 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how deeply a pandemic,

00:01:28.838 --> 00:01:33.843 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so-called natural disasters,
violence, and unrest

00:01:33.843 --> 00:01:36.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
would affect us economically,

00:01:36.045 --> 00:01:40.650 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
physically, and even emotionally?

00:01:40.650 --> 00:01:45.655 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of you dear friends
face unimaginable hardships.

00:01:45.655 --> 00:01:49.325 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many have experienced loss of loved ones,

00:01:49.325 --> 00:01:52.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
imprisonment, physical abuse,

00:01:52.228 --> 00:01:54.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
sickness, financial problems,

00:01:54.798 --> 00:01:57.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and sometimes a number of these

00:01:57.700 --> 00:02:02.205 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or other circumstances all at the same time.

00:02:02.205 --> 00:02:07.210 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You dear brothers and sisters
are in our prayers.

00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:10.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With this in mind, the theme for our program

00:02:10.113 --> 00:02:13.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is “In Difficult Times,

00:02:13.183 --> 00:02:17.253 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah Always Comforts.”

00:02:17.253 --> 00:02:20.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A scripture that’s become familiar
to Jehovah’s people

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:25.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is 2 Corinthians 1:3, 4:

00:02:26.629 --> 00:02:31.234 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Praised be the God and Father
of our Lord Jesus Christ,

00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:34.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“the Father of tender mercies

00:02:34.170 --> 00:02:36.873 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and the God of all comfort,

00:02:36.873 --> 00:02:39.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“who comforts us in all our trials

00:02:39.876 --> 00:02:42.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“so that we may be able to comfort others

00:02:42.512 --> 00:02:45.748 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in any sort of trial with the comfort

00:02:45.748 --> 00:02:48.318 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we receive from God.”

00:02:48.318 --> 00:02:51.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The <i>Study Bible </i> says this

00:02:51.621 --> 00:02:56.626 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
regarding the expression
“the Father of tender mercies”:

00:02:56.626 --> 00:02:59.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The Greek noun
rendered ‘tender mercies’ . . .

00:02:59.562 --> 00:03:03.399 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“is here used to describe a feeling
of compassion,

00:03:03.399 --> 00:03:05.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“or pity, for others.

00:03:05.702 --> 00:03:10.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“God is called <b>the Father,</b>
or the Source, <b>of tender mercies</b>

00:03:10.306 --> 00:03:15.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“because compassion emanates
from him and is part of his nature.

00:03:16.212 --> 00:03:19.048 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Such tender feelings move him

00:03:19.048 --> 00:03:22.752 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to act mercifully in behalf
of his faithful servants

00:03:22.752 --> 00:03:24.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who are suffering tribulation.”

00:03:26.489 --> 00:03:29.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Regarding the phrase,
“the God of all comfort,”

00:03:29.826 --> 00:03:34.430 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it continues: “The Greek noun . . .
here rendered ‘comfort,’

00:03:34.430 --> 00:03:37.867 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“literally means ‘a calling to one’s side.’

00:03:37.867 --> 00:03:41.371 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It conveys the idea
of standing next to a person,

00:03:41.371 --> 00:03:43.373 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“helping or encouraging him

00:03:43.373 --> 00:03:46.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“when he is undergoing trials
or feeling sad. . . .

00:03:46.542 --> 00:03:49.646 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“God uses his powerful active force

00:03:49.646 --> 00:03:53.349 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to give comfort and help in situations

00:03:53.349 --> 00:03:57.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that from a human viewpoint seem hopeless.”

00:03:58.254 --> 00:04:00.924 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Think about what that means.

00:04:00.924 --> 00:04:05.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah wants us to know
that whatever we face,

00:04:05.261 --> 00:04:08.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he is by our side, helping us

00:04:08.498 --> 00:04:11.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when we’re undergoing any sort of trial.

00:04:11.067 --> 00:04:14.971 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No, he did not promise
that he’d remove our trials.

00:04:14.971 --> 00:04:19.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Rather, he eases our misery, or grief,

00:04:19.008 --> 00:04:22.345 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
whenever we undergo difficulties.

00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:27.083 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a beautiful word picture
of God standing next to us,

00:04:27.083 --> 00:04:29.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
especially when things seem hopeless!

00:04:31.154 --> 00:04:34.590 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We invite you to do a personal study project.

00:04:34.590 --> 00:04:38.594 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Using the publication
<i>Research Guide for Jehovah’s Witnesses </i>

00:04:38.594 --> 00:04:41.297 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or the <i>Watchtower ONLINE LIBRARY™,</i>

00:04:41.297 --> 00:04:44.767 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
do a word search on “comfort.”

00:04:44.767 --> 00:04:48.905 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You will be drawn even closer to Jehovah

00:04:48.905 --> 00:04:52.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and appreciate his unmatched desire

00:04:52.141 --> 00:04:54.477 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and ability to comfort.

00:04:56.546 --> 00:04:59.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah also inspired Paul to show

00:04:59.415 --> 00:05:02.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how he would stand by us to comfort us.

00:05:04.520 --> 00:05:09.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Notice Romans 15:4:

00:05:09.525 --> 00:05:13.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<b>“</b>For all the things
that were written beforehand

00:05:13.896 --> 00:05:16.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“were written for our instruction,

00:05:16.499 --> 00:05:19.135 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“so that through our endurance

00:05:19.135 --> 00:05:22.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and through the comfort from the Scriptures

00:05:22.972 --> 00:05:25.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we might have hope.”

00:05:25.008 --> 00:05:28.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Comfort from the Scriptures”

00:05:28.177 --> 00:05:31.381 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—time limits us from going
into all of the ways

00:05:31.381 --> 00:05:33.616 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that the Bible does this.

00:05:33.616 --> 00:05:36.652 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But let’s take some examples.

00:05:36.652 --> 00:05:41.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A scripture that Jehovah’s people
have often meditated on in recent times

00:05:41.357 --> 00:05:45.094 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is found in Jeremiah chapter 29.

00:05:47.196 --> 00:05:52.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Jehovah inspired Jeremiah
to convey his message to the Jews,

00:05:52.201 --> 00:05:55.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they had been taken from Jerusalem

00:05:55.004 --> 00:05:58.007 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and were captives in Babylon.

00:05:58.007 --> 00:06:00.109 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They were downhearted.

00:06:00.109 --> 00:06:02.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But even while in captivity,

00:06:02.512 --> 00:06:05.948 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah provided a comforting message.

00:06:05.948 --> 00:06:08.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Notice his words

00:06:08.117 --> 00:06:10.987 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at Jeremiah 29:10:

00:06:10.987 --> 00:06:14.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled,

00:06:14.891 --> 00:06:18.061 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I will turn my attention to you.”

00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:21.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God told these Jewish exiles

00:06:21.464 --> 00:06:25.435 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that they would remain
in captivity for a long time.

00:06:25.435 --> 00:06:30.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then he made it clear to them
that he had a peaceful future in mind.

00:06:30.440 --> 00:06:33.342 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The latter part of that verse says:

00:06:33.342 --> 00:06:36.179 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And I will make good my promise

00:06:36.179 --> 00:06:38.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by bringing you back to this place.”

00:06:38.781 --> 00:06:40.783 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In verse 11, he says:

00:06:40.783 --> 00:06:42.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘I well know the thoughts

00:06:42.885 --> 00:06:44.420 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that I am thinking toward you,’

00:06:44.420 --> 00:06:47.490 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“declares Jehovah, ‘thoughts of peace,

00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:49.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘and not of calamity,

00:06:49.559 --> 00:06:53.496 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to give you a future and a hope.’”

00:06:53.496 --> 00:06:57.867 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God did make good
on his promise to those Israelites.

00:06:57.867 --> 00:07:02.105 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He let them know
that their future was to be a bright one.

00:07:02.105 --> 00:07:06.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Regarding Jeremiah 29:11,

00:07:06.542 --> 00:07:10.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
one commentary states:

00:07:10.113 --> 00:07:14.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It is difficult to find
a more wonderful promise

00:07:14.183 --> 00:07:18.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“anywhere in Scripture
that expresses the tender compassion

00:07:18.821 --> 00:07:21.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of Yahweh [Jehovah]

00:07:21.357 --> 00:07:24.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“toward these exiles
and setting before them, at last,

00:07:24.894 --> 00:07:29.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a real reason for optimism and expectation.”

00:07:29.866 --> 00:07:32.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah’s promise strengthened men

00:07:32.935 --> 00:07:37.607 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
such as Jeremiah, Ezekiel, and Daniel.

00:07:37.607 --> 00:07:41.677 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah reassured the Jews
by repeating his promise

00:07:41.677 --> 00:07:45.214 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at Jeremiah 31:17:

00:07:45.214 --> 00:07:48.718 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And there is a hope for your future . . .

00:07:48.718 --> 00:07:52.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your sons will return
to their own territory.”

00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:58.294 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sure enough, just as Jehovah foretold,

00:07:58.294 --> 00:08:01.964 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Babylon was conquered
by the Persian King Cyrus,

00:08:01.964 --> 00:08:05.968 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who allowed the exiled Jews
to return to their homeland.

00:08:05.968 --> 00:08:09.005 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
After 70 years of captivity,

00:08:09.005 --> 00:08:11.507 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they were back in Jerusalem.

00:08:11.507 --> 00:08:15.478 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah ‘made good on his promise.’

00:08:16.812 --> 00:08:20.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What does that have to do with us today?

00:08:20.383 --> 00:08:24.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The fulfilled promises of Jehovah assure us

00:08:24.854 --> 00:08:28.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that his promises to us will come true

00:08:28.591 --> 00:08:31.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in spite of surrounding circumstances.

00:08:31.160 --> 00:08:35.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As he said: “I will make good my promise.”

00:08:35.498 --> 00:08:37.967 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How comforting to know that!

00:08:37.967 --> 00:08:42.705 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But we know that the greatest expression
of Jehovah’s comfort

00:08:42.705 --> 00:08:47.510 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is his only-begotten Son, Jesus.

00:08:47.510 --> 00:08:51.080 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
During his time on earth,
he gave people hope.

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:54.450 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus engaged in a marvelous ministry

00:08:54.450 --> 00:08:57.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—healing the sick, performing powerful works

00:08:57.320 --> 00:09:01.924 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and, most important,
teaching people about God’s Kingdom.

00:09:03.292 --> 00:09:08.297 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, the greatest expression
of hope to us humans

00:09:08.297 --> 00:09:11.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is Jesus’ ransom sacrifice.

00:09:12.568 --> 00:09:15.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Through his inspired Word,

00:09:15.238 --> 00:09:18.841 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can see that Jehovah assures us

00:09:18.841 --> 00:09:22.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he not only understands what we face

00:09:22.678 --> 00:09:27.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but also desires
to console and strengthen us.

00:09:27.617 --> 00:09:30.086 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our loving heavenly Father

00:09:30.086 --> 00:09:34.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
especially watches over all
who endeavor to do his will.

00:09:34.123 --> 00:09:36.492 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But in all of his mercy,

00:09:36.492 --> 00:09:40.763 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he also draws humble people
who may not yet know him.

00:09:41.731 --> 00:09:45.034 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How many of us were in dire straits

00:09:45.034 --> 00:09:47.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
only to be introduced to the truth

00:09:47.303 --> 00:09:51.207 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and to get to know Jehovah at the right time?

00:09:51.207 --> 00:09:53.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That was no coincidence.

00:09:53.409 --> 00:09:56.846 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s a consequence of Jehovah’s love

00:09:56.846 --> 00:10:01.083 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and his desire to give people comfort
through the hope he provides.

00:10:03.452 --> 00:10:06.088 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Dear brothers and sisters,

00:10:06.088 --> 00:10:10.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as we get closer to the great tribulation,

00:10:10.259 --> 00:10:13.763 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we will face more distressing circumstances.

00:10:13.763 --> 00:10:16.032 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And during the great tribulation,

00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:19.802 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our trust in Jehovah must be solid.

00:10:19.802 --> 00:10:22.905 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We need to be sensitive
and receptive to the ways

00:10:22.905 --> 00:10:25.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in which he consoles and strengthens us.

00:10:25.441 --> 00:10:28.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We need to keep in mind what Paul says

00:10:28.678 --> 00:10:31.814 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at 2 Corinthians 1:4,

00:10:31.814 --> 00:10:34.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
perhaps even memorizing it.

00:10:34.116 --> 00:10:36.285 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is a God

00:10:36.285 --> 00:10:40.189 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“who comforts us in all our trials.”

00:10:43.459 --> 00:10:46.462 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some time ago,
we interviewed two longtime members

00:10:46.462 --> 00:10:49.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the United States Bethel family:

00:10:49.231 --> 00:10:51.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Gerald Grizzle,

00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:53.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a helper to the Personnel Committee,

00:10:53.969 --> 00:10:56.339 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Brother Sam Roberson.

00:10:56.339 --> 00:10:58.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These two brothers served
as traveling overseers

00:10:58.808 --> 00:11:01.744 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for many years prior to coming to Bethel.

00:11:01.744 --> 00:11:06.148 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Grizzle has served
at Bethel since 1978,

00:11:06.148 --> 00:11:10.886 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Brother Roberson
has served here for nearly 20 years.

00:11:10.886 --> 00:11:13.322 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They’ve been assigned
by the Governing Body

00:11:13.322 --> 00:11:17.893 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to assist them in shepherding
the United States Bethel family.

00:11:17.893 --> 00:11:20.296 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Shepherding the Bethel family?’ you may ask.

00:11:20.296 --> 00:11:24.867 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘After all, Bethelites
don’t have any distressing trials!’

00:11:24.867 --> 00:11:28.237 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Listen to what our dear brothers have to say.

00:11:28.237 --> 00:11:31.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Grizzle,
what are some of the challenges

00:11:31.807 --> 00:11:34.143 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that members of the Bethel family face?

00:11:34.143 --> 00:11:36.812 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
The worldwide Bethel family

00:11:36.812 --> 00:11:41.584 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
is a representation of the brotherhood.

00:11:41.584 --> 00:11:43.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
By that I mean that

00:11:43.753 --> 00:11:47.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
just as 1 Peter 5:9 says,

00:11:47.923 --> 00:11:50.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they face ‘the same kind of sufferings

00:11:50.926 --> 00:11:54.463 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘being experienced by the entire association

00:11:54.463 --> 00:11:56.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of our brothers in the world.’

00:11:56.465 --> 00:12:00.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some deal with serious health problems,

00:12:00.703 --> 00:12:03.806 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but they continue to serve.

00:12:03.806 --> 00:12:05.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Others

00:12:05.808 --> 00:12:09.345 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have concerns over aging parents,

00:12:09.345 --> 00:12:14.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and some have to give up
their beloved Bethel service.

00:12:15.017 --> 00:12:19.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Still others contend
with bouts of depression.

00:12:19.622 --> 00:12:23.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the spirit
of these dear brothers and sisters

00:12:23.926 --> 00:12:28.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
impels them to have the determination

00:12:28.330 --> 00:12:32.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not to allow these challenges
to dominate them.

00:12:32.334 --> 00:12:34.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Rather, their faith in Jehovah

00:12:34.837 --> 00:12:37.840 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
strengthens their resolve

00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:40.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to focus on their assignments.

00:12:40.509 --> 00:12:41.877 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thank you for that insight,

00:12:41.877 --> 00:12:43.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Grizzle.

00:12:43.913 --> 00:12:48.250 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Roberson, how have you been able
to comfort such ones?

00:12:48.250 --> 00:12:50.986 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
When we find out a Bethelite

00:12:50.986 --> 00:12:53.022 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
is going through a tragedy,

00:12:53.022 --> 00:12:55.324 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
there are four things that we do.

00:12:55.324 --> 00:12:58.761 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Number one, we pray for them

00:12:58.761 --> 00:13:01.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and develop specific spiritual points

00:13:01.730 --> 00:13:04.333 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
according to their needs.

00:13:04.333 --> 00:13:07.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that’s before we make the call.

00:13:07.136 --> 00:13:10.139 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Number two, when we actually make the call,

00:13:10.139 --> 00:13:11.841 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we really listen.

00:13:11.841 --> 00:13:14.743 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I don’t mean
we just listen with our ears.

00:13:15.511 --> 00:13:17.980 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We try to listen with our hearts.

00:13:17.980 --> 00:13:20.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We try to feel what they feel.

00:13:20.850 --> 00:13:23.419 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We try to have compassion.

00:13:23.419 --> 00:13:28.090 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Number three, when we use God’s Word

00:13:28.090 --> 00:13:31.360 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to remind them
they’re not facing their crisis alone,

00:13:31.360 --> 00:13:33.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is very effective.

00:13:33.362 --> 00:13:36.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As an example,
we called on a brother recently

00:13:36.532 --> 00:13:39.134 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who was going through a great trial,

00:13:39.134 --> 00:13:41.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we shared, among other things,

00:13:41.136 --> 00:13:45.474 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Exodus 3:7, 12.

00:13:45.474 --> 00:13:47.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s take a look at that:

00:13:47.576 --> 00:13:50.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I have certainly seen the affliction

00:13:50.312 --> 00:13:52.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“of my people who are in Egypt,

00:13:52.815 --> 00:13:54.817 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and I have heard their outcry

00:13:54.817 --> 00:13:57.887 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because of those who force them to work.”

00:13:57.887 --> 00:14:02.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And note the ending point here
—it’s very beautiful.

00:14:02.224 --> 00:14:07.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah doesn’t say,
‘I know how my people feel’;

00:14:07.229 --> 00:14:09.598 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he says: “I <i>well </i> know

00:14:09.598 --> 00:14:12.268 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the pains [of my people].”

00:14:12.268 --> 00:14:15.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then in giving assurance

00:14:15.170 --> 00:14:18.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
dealing with Moses
fearing to go before Pharaoh,

00:14:18.974 --> 00:14:22.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in verse 12, just the <i>A</i>  part:

00:14:22.378 --> 00:14:27.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“To this he said:
‘I will prove to be with you.’”

00:14:28.484 --> 00:14:31.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s just a few words but so powerful,

00:14:31.587 --> 00:14:34.590 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where Jehovah is guaranteeing

00:14:34.590 --> 00:14:39.595 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he’s going to give them undeniable proof

00:14:39.595 --> 00:14:44.600 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he’s backing them up
and never moving away from them one inch.

00:14:44.600 --> 00:14:46.602 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And this gives us comfort.

00:14:46.602 --> 00:14:48.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, number four,

00:14:48.704 --> 00:14:51.574 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
before we conclude the call,

00:14:51.574 --> 00:14:54.310 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we have an ending prayer with them.

00:14:54.310 --> 00:14:56.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we use their names,

00:14:56.512 --> 00:14:59.949 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and this is very comforting
since we’re calling on Jehovah,

00:14:59.949 --> 00:15:01.951 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Great Shepherd.

00:15:01.951 --> 00:15:04.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At 1 Thessalonians 5:14,

00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:07.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Paul says: “We urge you, brothers, to . . .

00:15:07.222 --> 00:15:10.626 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“speak consolingly to those
who are depressed,

00:15:10.626 --> 00:15:14.430 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
[to] support the weak,
be patient toward all.”

00:15:14.430 --> 00:15:16.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And this is exactly what we’re trying to do.

00:15:17.666 --> 00:15:21.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thanks for sharing those thoughts
—very interesting.

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:24.940 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brothers Grizzle and Roberson:

00:15:24.940 --> 00:15:27.643 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How has comforting others affected you?

00:15:27.643 --> 00:15:29.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Grizzle first, please.

00:15:29.645 --> 00:15:32.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
During these challenging times,

00:15:32.781 --> 00:15:36.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I sense Jehovah’s love for his people.

00:15:36.952 --> 00:15:38.954 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Over the years,

00:15:38.954 --> 00:15:43.092 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I have seen and experienced his care

00:15:43.092 --> 00:15:46.629 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when facing difficult times.

00:15:46.629 --> 00:15:48.631 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some years ago,

00:15:48.631 --> 00:15:52.968 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I lost my mother, my brother,

00:15:52.968 --> 00:15:57.973 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and my father in death all within a year.

00:15:57.973 --> 00:16:00.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And in 2017,

00:16:00.876 --> 00:16:04.079 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I lost my dear wife, Bonnie,

00:16:04.079 --> 00:16:07.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
after we had served Jehovah together

00:16:07.082 --> 00:16:10.586 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for nearly 65 years.

00:16:10.586 --> 00:16:12.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But with much prayer,

00:16:12.621 --> 00:16:16.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
research, and love of the friends,

00:16:16.358 --> 00:16:19.094 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has comforted me.

00:16:19.094 --> 00:16:21.230 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And now, thankfully,

00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:24.333 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I have been able
to offer encouragement to others.

00:16:24.600 --> 00:16:25.601 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Very touching, Brother Grizzle,

00:16:25.601 --> 00:16:26.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
thank you.

00:16:28.003 --> 00:16:31.073 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Roberson,
how has comforting others

00:16:31.073 --> 00:16:33.075 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
affected you?

00:16:33.075 --> 00:16:35.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One of the most memorable challenges

00:16:35.611 --> 00:16:37.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was while my wife, Linda, and I
were in the circuit work

00:16:37.913 --> 00:16:40.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
several years ago.

00:16:40.049 --> 00:16:42.284 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I lost my voice.

00:16:42.284 --> 00:16:45.087 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I had to have surgery on my vocal cords,

00:16:45.087 --> 00:16:48.757 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and for six weeks, I could not talk.

00:16:48.757 --> 00:16:52.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For a circuit overseer,
that’s like being a bird without its wings.

00:16:53.862 --> 00:16:57.066 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wrote more notes in that six weeks

00:16:57.066 --> 00:17:00.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
than I had written in my whole life!

00:17:00.002 --> 00:17:04.673 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But in spite of that
and along with other situations and tragedies

00:17:04.673 --> 00:17:07.376 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we faced similar to Gerald’s,

00:17:07.376 --> 00:17:10.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has seen us through them all.

00:17:10.312 --> 00:17:12.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And let me say, it’s been a real pleasure

00:17:12.715 --> 00:17:16.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to share Jehovah’s comfort with so many.

00:17:16.385 --> 00:17:19.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And as we do,
we see the Governing Body’s interest

00:17:19.788 --> 00:17:21.790 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in all of Jehovah’s people,

00:17:21.790 --> 00:17:24.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
including those with added responsibility.

00:17:24.927 --> 00:17:28.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They truly reflect Jehovah’s feelings

00:17:28.097 --> 00:17:30.966 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as “the God of all comfort.”

00:17:30.966 --> 00:17:33.035 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, thank you, brothers.

00:17:33.035 --> 00:17:35.571 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We really appreciate your comments.

00:17:35.571 --> 00:17:39.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And more than the shepherding that you do

00:17:39.441 --> 00:17:42.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is the example that you have set

00:17:42.311 --> 00:17:44.480 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in enduring trials,

00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:46.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in experiencing Jehovah’s comfort,

00:17:46.815 --> 00:17:48.650 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and in comforting others.

00:17:48.650 --> 00:17:49.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thank you so much.

00:17:51.653 --> 00:17:55.657 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Governing Body has instituted
similar shepherding arrangements

00:17:55.657 --> 00:17:58.627 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in branch offices around the world.

00:18:00.796 --> 00:18:04.466 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now we want to talk
to some of you in our audience.

00:18:05.601 --> 00:18:09.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because of stresses, disappointments,

00:18:09.505 --> 00:18:13.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and hurt feelings caused by fellow believers,

00:18:13.041 --> 00:18:17.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some have strayed
from Jehovah’s organization.

00:18:17.012 --> 00:18:20.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Others may have been removed
from the congregation

00:18:20.182 --> 00:18:23.452 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but now would like to return.

00:18:23.452 --> 00:18:25.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To you we say:

00:18:25.687 --> 00:18:29.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Allow Jehovah to comfort and strengthen you.

00:18:29.391 --> 00:18:34.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He wants you to draw close to him,
and he will help you.”

00:18:35.764 --> 00:18:38.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
James 4:8 says:

00:18:38.834 --> 00:18:41.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Draw close to God,

00:18:41.570 --> 00:18:43.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he will draw close to you.”

00:18:45.174 --> 00:18:49.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has great care for such ones.

00:18:49.144 --> 00:18:51.146 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s read what he says

00:18:51.146 --> 00:18:56.084 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at Ezekiel 34:16:

00:18:56.084 --> 00:19:00.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The stray I will bring back,

00:19:00.289 --> 00:19:03.225 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“the injured I will bandage,

00:19:03.225 --> 00:19:06.695 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the weak I will strengthen.”

00:19:06.695 --> 00:19:08.864 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some who have recovered have said

00:19:08.864 --> 00:19:11.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that one of the most
difficult things for them to do

00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:14.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was to cross the threshold
of the Kingdom Hall.

00:19:14.770 --> 00:19:19.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But remember, it’s Jehovah who bandages you,

00:19:19.341 --> 00:19:23.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his sheep, helping you to heal.

00:19:23.145 --> 00:19:27.516 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the same chapter, in verse 12, he says:

00:19:27.516 --> 00:19:31.987 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I will care for my sheep . . . 

00:19:31.987 --> 00:19:35.290 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I will rescue them from all the places

00:19:35.290 --> 00:19:37.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where they were scattered.”

00:19:38.427 --> 00:19:43.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In imitation of that love,
the faithful slave says,

00:19:43.298 --> 00:19:47.202 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We view you as lost sheep,

00:19:47.202 --> 00:19:49.304 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not a lost cause.”

00:19:50.505 --> 00:19:52.507 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To all we say,

00:19:52.507 --> 00:19:55.310 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“No matter what you face, remember:

00:19:55.310 --> 00:19:57.446 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In difficult times,

00:19:57.446 --> 00:20:00.716 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah always comforts.”

00:20:03.118 --> 00:20:05.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Throughout our program,
we’ll hear experiences

00:20:05.821 --> 00:20:10.092 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of brothers and sisters
who were comforted by Jehovah.

00:20:10.092 --> 00:20:12.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As they share their stories,

00:20:12.261 --> 00:20:15.230 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
look for all the ways Jehovah helped them

00:20:15.230 --> 00:20:17.966 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and consider how you can help others.

00:20:18.834 --> 00:20:21.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First is the experience of Maombi Vianney.

00:25:23.838 --> 00:25:26.741 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you’re suffering some kind of trial

00:25:26.741 --> 00:25:29.344 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you’re searching for God,

00:25:29.344 --> 00:25:32.514 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
be encouraged by Maombi’s story.

00:25:32.514 --> 00:25:34.849 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah knows your struggles,

00:25:34.849 --> 00:25:37.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he draws all deserving ones to him.

00:25:39.087 --> 00:25:41.156 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you notice that Maombi,

00:25:41.156 --> 00:25:43.158 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
having received comfort,

00:25:43.158 --> 00:25:45.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was moved to help others?

00:25:45.994 --> 00:25:47.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In our next segment,

00:25:47.996 --> 00:25:52.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’ll see just how powerful
the love of our brothers and sisters can be.

00:26:09.551 --> 00:26:12.721 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
LaQuita worked
for the City of Virginia Beach.

00:26:12.721 --> 00:26:16.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With the city, she was able to get a schedule

00:26:16.491 --> 00:26:20.328 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that allowed her to focus on her ministry.

00:26:22.397 --> 00:26:25.133 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
I came home on a Friday.

00:26:26.635 --> 00:26:27.769 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Both my mother and I had

00:26:27.769 --> 00:26:29.571 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
doctors’ appointments that day.

00:26:30.305 --> 00:26:32.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we came home and sat down,

00:26:32.407 --> 00:26:35.010 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
getting ready to fix us a bite of lunch,

00:26:35.010 --> 00:26:37.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I got a phone call.

00:26:37.445 --> 00:26:40.849 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was a family member,

00:26:40.849 --> 00:26:44.219 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they were asking me
if I had seen the news.

00:26:44.219 --> 00:26:47.188 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I immediately

00:26:47.188 --> 00:26:49.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
tried to call my daughter’s phone,

00:26:50.525 --> 00:26:52.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and it went straight to voice mail.

00:26:52.927 --> 00:26:56.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I said, “Well, let me try texting her.”

00:26:56.298 --> 00:26:58.967 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I tried texting her,

00:26:58.967 --> 00:27:01.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I didn’t get any response.

00:27:02.971 --> 00:27:05.607 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was about 10:00 or 10:30

00:27:07.342 --> 00:27:10.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that night when we just finally
got the confirmation

00:27:10.545 --> 00:27:14.316 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we had indeed lost her in that shooting.

00:27:18.053 --> 00:27:20.488 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I will say,
that was the worst day of my life.

00:27:24.559 --> 00:27:26.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The next day,

00:27:28.129 --> 00:27:31.533 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
starting at seven o’clock in the morning,

00:27:31.533 --> 00:27:33.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
friends started pouring in,

00:27:33.868 --> 00:27:35.970 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we had

00:27:35.970 --> 00:27:39.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
people in our home

00:27:39.407 --> 00:27:41.910 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to support us and encourage us

00:27:41.910 --> 00:27:44.079 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from morning till night.

00:27:50.018 --> 00:27:52.887 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And it meant so much.

00:27:54.556 --> 00:27:58.526 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It helped us to focus

00:27:58.526 --> 00:28:01.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
