00:36:36.444 --> 00:36:40.348 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When I was growing up,
my parents always used to say:

00:36:40.348 --> 00:36:42.683 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Pray about your spiritual goals.

00:36:45.319 --> 00:36:47.355 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Work hard.

00:36:49.724 --> 00:36:53.227 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then let Jehovah do the rest.”

00:36:57.365 --> 00:36:59.600 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So that’s what I did.

00:37:01.469 --> 00:37:05.139 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And wow, did Jehovah pour out the blessings!

00:37:07.308 --> 00:37:10.745 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I even got invited
to a branch construction project.

00:37:11.579 --> 00:37:14.215 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I was pretty excited

00:37:14.215 --> 00:37:15.883 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at first.

00:37:18.019 --> 00:37:19.353 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t get me wrong.

00:37:19.353 --> 00:37:22.089 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was a privilege to be there,

00:37:22.089 --> 00:37:25.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but the work was harder
than I thought it would be.

00:37:29.864 --> 00:37:32.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There were a lot of new skills to learn.

00:37:34.101 --> 00:37:38.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I have to admit,
I really wanted to impress my overseer.

00:37:40.675 --> 00:37:42.977 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I pushed hard,

00:37:46.280 --> 00:37:48.749 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
maybe a little too hard.

00:37:51.585 --> 00:37:53.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you see all that up there?

00:37:53.621 --> 00:37:55.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That all needs to come down.

00:37:55.256 --> 00:37:55.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK.

00:37:55.923 --> 00:37:57.959 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you think you can wrap this up
before tomorrow?

00:37:57.959 --> 00:38:00.061 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sure thing. I’m on it.

00:38:00.061 --> 00:38:03.230 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can grab Jin and Young
to give you a hand with the lift.

00:38:03.230 --> 00:38:05.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jin’s a pro; he’ll help you out.

00:38:05.232 --> 00:38:06.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Got it.

00:38:07.802 --> 00:38:10.237 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The job didn’t look that hard.

00:38:10.237 --> 00:38:13.207 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And, I mean, I had the training.

00:38:13.207 --> 00:38:16.644 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So if I had waited for them,

00:38:16.644 --> 00:38:19.714 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there was no way
we were going to get this done today.

00:38:56.450 --> 00:39:01.088 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The fact is, I had caused some real damage,

00:39:01.088 --> 00:39:03.991 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I made more work for everyone.

00:39:06.127 --> 00:39:08.429 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ian, are you OK?

00:39:08.429 --> 00:39:10.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, I’m fine.

00:39:10.498 --> 00:39:12.600 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you have a minute to talk in my office?

00:39:12.600 --> 00:39:13.467 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yeah.

00:39:19.640 --> 00:39:21.776 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I felt like such a loser.

00:39:30.184 --> 00:39:33.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The brothers talked to me,
and they were nice about it.

00:39:33.320 --> 00:39:35.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But I was still left thinking:

00:39:35.656 --> 00:39:37.691 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘What am I doing here?

00:39:37.691 --> 00:39:39.960 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe I should just go home.’

00:39:40.828 --> 00:39:42.663 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
James 3:2 says:

00:39:42.663 --> 00:39:46.867 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“For we all stumble many times.”

00:39:46.867 --> 00:39:48.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the real question is,

00:39:48.869 --> 00:39:52.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When we stumble
—and it is going to happen—

00:39:52.540 --> 00:39:54.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
what should we do then?

00:39:56.544 --> 00:39:58.579 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, Jake.

00:40:00.014 --> 00:40:03.517 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, when Dad was teaching me
to ride my bike,

00:40:03.517 --> 00:40:05.319 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I fell a lot.

00:40:05.319 --> 00:40:06.987 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And it was hard.

00:40:06.987 --> 00:40:10.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But I just kept getting up and trying again.

00:40:10.357 --> 00:40:14.161 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And now I can ride pretty fast!

00:40:14.161 --> 00:40:17.364 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So you just have to get back up
when you fall.

00:40:17.364 --> 00:40:20.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, that’s right!
That was a great comment.

00:40:21.569 --> 00:40:24.738 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wow, Jake, that’s it!

00:40:24.738 --> 00:40:28.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I had to swallow my pride
and just get back up.

00:40:35.015 --> 00:40:37.518 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I realized I needed to be more focused

00:40:37.518 --> 00:40:41.922 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on the seriousness of my assignment
and not so focused on myself.

00:40:44.558 --> 00:40:47.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And instead of trying to do
everything myself,

00:40:47.895 --> 00:40:50.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I set more realistic expectations

00:40:50.464 --> 00:40:53.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about what I could do and what I couldn’t.

00:40:56.770 --> 00:40:58.939 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I had a lot to learn.

00:40:59.874 --> 00:41:02.743 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I kept working and learning.

00:41:04.912 --> 00:41:07.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And after a while,

00:41:07.314 --> 00:41:11.218 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I even got to help train
some of the new volunteers.

00:41:13.053 --> 00:41:16.323 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the end, I was so thankful to Jehovah

00:41:16.323 --> 00:41:20.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for helping me understand
that in the race for life,

00:41:20.261 --> 00:41:23.964 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
none of us are going to cross the finish line
without stumbling.

00:41:24.999 --> 00:41:29.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The important thing
is to get back up and just keep going.

00:41:32.940 --> 00:41:35.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some hesitate to draw close to people

00:41:35.409 --> 00:41:38.112 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of different races or nationalities.

00:41:38.112 --> 00:41:42.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But they can overcome this
by imitating Jehovah’s impartiality.

00:41:42.049 --> 00:41:43.784 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The result?

00:41:43.784 --> 00:41:45.786 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Great joy.

00:41:45.786 --> 00:41:48.789 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’ll see an example
of this in the following report.

00:41:55.396 --> 00:41:58.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On September 18, 2020,

00:41:58.232 --> 00:41:59.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Medicane Ianos,

00:41:59.667 --> 00:42:03.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a rare Mediterranean cyclone, struck Greece

00:42:03.170 --> 00:42:05.773 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and flooded a Roma settlement in Mavrika,

00:42:05.773 --> 00:42:08.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
just outside the city of Karditsa.

00:42:11.078 --> 00:42:14.682 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Local authorities worked
alongside emergency services to evacuate

00:42:14.682 --> 00:42:17.151 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
over 1,000 Roma who lived there.

00:42:17.151 --> 00:42:18.752 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
But a family of seven

00:42:18.752 --> 00:42:20.821 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
who are studying with Jehovah’s Witnesses

00:42:20.821 --> 00:42:22.823 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
were left behind.

00:42:24.191 --> 00:42:25.960 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
It was raining hard,

00:42:25.960 --> 00:42:28.329 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and the floodwaters were rising quickly.

00:42:28.329 --> 00:42:29.997 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
I took my wife by the hand

00:42:29.997 --> 00:42:32.266 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and carried my child on my back.

00:42:32.266 --> 00:42:36.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With great difficulty, we managed
to make it to a neighboring house.

00:42:36.470 --> 00:42:39.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We were unable to contact the authorities.

00:42:39.340 --> 00:42:42.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We were terrified
and had no option but to stay there.

00:42:42.876 --> 00:42:45.546 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
We didn’t know what to do.

00:42:45.546 --> 00:42:47.815 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
We were so scared and worried.

00:42:47.815 --> 00:42:49.450 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
We had never experienced

00:42:49.450 --> 00:42:51.151 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
anything like this before.

00:42:51.151 --> 00:42:53.821 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
The floodwaters had risen a lot,

00:42:53.821 --> 00:42:56.523 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and we stood waiting for hours.

00:42:56.523 --> 00:42:59.159 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
I asked my father to pray for us.

00:42:59.159 --> 00:43:02.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He did many times.

00:43:02.529 --> 00:43:06.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There were lots of people in the house,
both young and old.

00:43:06.500 --> 00:43:09.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They were afraid, and they were crying.

00:43:14.808 --> 00:43:19.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Video messages from the family
started to come through, asking for help.

00:43:19.546 --> 00:43:21.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We could see their fear.

00:43:21.548 --> 00:43:23.550 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We wanted to help them,

00:43:23.550 --> 00:43:27.721 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but there was no way for us to go there
because access was impossible.

00:43:28.922 --> 00:43:31.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All we could do was pray to Jehovah for them

00:43:31.692 --> 00:43:33.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and send messages of encouragement.

00:43:34.862 --> 00:43:36.964 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We were very distressed.

00:43:36.964 --> 00:43:38.966 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Children were crying.

00:43:38.966 --> 00:43:42.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I prayed to Jehovah,
begging him for peace of mind.

00:43:42.936 --> 00:43:46.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I threw all of my burdens
and anxiety of my heart on Jehovah.

00:43:46.807 --> 00:43:51.278 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Soon, I felt calm and had no anxiety.

00:43:51.278 --> 00:43:56.283 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I felt his spirit giving me strength
during the hours that followed until dawn.

00:44:12.299 --> 00:44:14.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The situation was very difficult.

00:44:14.868 --> 00:44:16.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They had suffered a lot,

00:44:16.303 --> 00:44:18.339 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and their clothes were dirty.

00:44:18.339 --> 00:44:19.873 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
There was no way

00:44:19.873 --> 00:44:21.709 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
that I could leave them there.

00:44:23.077 --> 00:44:25.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We were given a house to stay in.

00:44:26.780 --> 00:44:29.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We were able to calm down and sleep.

00:44:29.917 --> 00:44:31.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The brothers gave us food.

00:44:31.919 --> 00:44:35.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I thanked Jehovah for teaching us
and taking care of us.

00:44:36.890 --> 00:44:39.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He is our Savior.

00:44:40.728 --> 00:44:45.733 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When I attended the first meeting
after the flood, I felt calm again.

00:44:45.733 --> 00:44:49.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I tried to keep my routine as normal:

00:44:49.002 --> 00:44:53.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
study, meetings, preparing comments.

00:44:53.974 --> 00:44:56.443 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I felt joy and contentment.

00:44:56.443 --> 00:45:01.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My legal documents, such as my ID,
were saved from the flood.

00:45:01.115 --> 00:45:04.017 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our neighbors were not prepared.

00:45:04.017 --> 00:45:06.286 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But we, thanks to Jehovah’s direction,

00:45:06.286 --> 00:45:08.288 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had packed emergency bags.

00:45:09.289 --> 00:45:13.127 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
About a week later,
we were able to return to Mavrika.

00:45:13.127 --> 00:45:16.830 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The houses were in terrible condition,
full of mud.

00:45:18.365 --> 00:45:22.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Disaster Relief Committee
helped us immediately.

00:45:22.136 --> 00:45:26.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brothers from 300 kilometers (190 mi) away
sent emergency supplies.

00:45:27.708 --> 00:45:31.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The brotherhood showed us love in practice.

00:45:31.145 --> 00:45:34.948 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They worked hard
and helped us because they love us.

00:45:34.948 --> 00:45:37.718 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I was deeply touched and found myself in awe.

00:45:37.718 --> 00:45:39.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We are united.

00:45:39.386 --> 00:45:43.290 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All of this brought
glory and praise to Jehovah.

00:45:44.858 --> 00:45:48.862 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When we went there to help,
the Roma neighbors were very surprised.

00:45:48.862 --> 00:45:51.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They asked if we could help them too.

00:45:51.231 --> 00:45:56.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We replied that we have to help
our family first, our brothers.

00:45:56.170 --> 00:45:59.640 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They were very puzzled
that we called our Roma brothers family

00:45:59.640 --> 00:46:01.842 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
since we were not from their tribe.

00:46:04.011 --> 00:46:08.849 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ephesians 4:16 finds a good application
in this story.

00:46:08.849 --> 00:46:12.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Just as every joint in the body offers help,

00:46:13.020 --> 00:46:15.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so did the brothers.

00:46:16.056 --> 00:46:18.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We all worked together

00:46:18.091 --> 00:46:21.028 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to provide help to our brothers in need.

00:46:23.063 --> 00:46:26.166 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is teaching me and helping me.

00:46:26.166 --> 00:46:28.168 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I really trust in him.

00:46:28.168 --> 00:46:30.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He has blessed me personally.

00:46:30.704 --> 00:46:33.707 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I have seen how good he is to me.

00:46:33.707 --> 00:46:37.277 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In a miserable world, Jehovah brings me joy.

00:46:37.277 --> 00:46:41.215 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I know that he chooses
according to a person’s heart.

00:46:41.215 --> 00:46:44.251 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All glory belongs to Jehovah!

00:46:48.489 --> 00:46:50.324 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In total,

00:46:50.324 --> 00:46:53.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
seven members of the Tsakiris family
are studying the Bible.

00:46:53.927 --> 00:46:55.929 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Five, who are deaf,

00:46:55.929 --> 00:46:58.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are studying
with a Greek Sign Language group.

00:46:59.132 --> 00:47:01.134 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When the flood struck,

00:47:01.134 --> 00:47:05.005 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about 20 people,
including the Tsakiris family,

00:47:05.005 --> 00:47:08.342 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
could not be evacuated
because of strong currents.

00:47:08.342 --> 00:47:13.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At first, other Roma who had been left behind
blamed the flood on the family

00:47:13.113 --> 00:47:16.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because they were all studying
with Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:47:16.950 --> 00:47:21.822 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But after they observed the assistance
provided by the brothers and sisters,

00:47:21.822 --> 00:47:25.459 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they said:
“You have the true religion.

00:47:25.459 --> 00:47:27.528 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You show genuine love.”

00:47:29.496 --> 00:47:32.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our series “My Teen Life”

00:47:32.499 --> 00:47:34.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has helped many young Witnesses

00:47:34.701 --> 00:47:37.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
navigate today’s realities.

00:47:37.671 --> 00:47:42.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our next episode has to do with association,

00:47:42.009 --> 00:47:44.478 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we’ll hear from a brother and a sister

00:47:44.478 --> 00:47:46.547 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who eventually made good decisions

00:47:46.547 --> 00:47:49.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with the help of Bible principles.

00:47:49.182 --> 00:47:51.485 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That may not surprise you.

00:47:51.485 --> 00:47:55.756 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what we’re looking for in this is “how.”

00:47:55.756 --> 00:48:00.727 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How did they go from knowing Bible principles
to applying them?

00:48:11.238 --> 00:48:13.307 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
My parents were both Jehovah’s Witnesses

00:48:13.307 --> 00:48:14.875 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
by the time I was born.

00:48:14.875 --> 00:48:16.877 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I studied the Bible,

00:48:16.877 --> 00:48:19.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
attended meetings,
and went out in service with them.

00:48:21.615 --> 00:48:23.717 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Growing up in the truth, I knew

00:48:23.717 --> 00:48:26.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that living by Bible standards
is what’s best for me.

00:48:26.753 --> 00:48:28.855 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And my parents were always so zealous

00:48:28.855 --> 00:48:31.158 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when it came to spiritual things.

00:48:31.158 --> 00:48:33.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So when I think back,

00:48:33.160 --> 00:48:35.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I just didn’t want to let them down.

00:48:36.463 --> 00:48:39.733 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Following Bible principles is not burdensome

00:48:39.733 --> 00:48:41.101 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or even that difficult.

00:48:42.402 --> 00:48:46.206 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Honestly, if we do as it says in the Bible,
then we benefit ourselves.

00:48:47.074 --> 00:48:49.743 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But at times, I was curious

00:48:49.743 --> 00:48:52.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how my life would be
if I wasn’t in the truth.

00:48:52.946 --> 00:48:56.783 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was just so fun
to be around my school friends.

00:48:56.783 --> 00:49:00.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Overall, I had a good time at school.

00:49:00.621 --> 00:49:03.991 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I got along with my classmates, 
and my teachers liked me too.

00:49:03.991 --> 00:49:07.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So being in school
was a pretty good experience.

00:49:07.160 --> 00:49:12.099 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My parents always told me
not to get too close to my classmates,

00:49:12.099 --> 00:49:14.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but in my opinion, my friends

00:49:14.267 --> 00:49:17.137 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had good conduct and were good people.

00:49:17.137 --> 00:49:20.107 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I didn’t understand why they were so worried.

00:49:20.107 --> 00:49:22.075 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In my high school,

00:49:22.075 --> 00:49:24.978 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there were a lot of kids who went to church

00:49:24.978 --> 00:49:27.481 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and many of the teachers
had religious backgrounds.

00:49:27.481 --> 00:49:31.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One day, there was an incident
when the entire school found out

00:49:31.952 --> 00:49:34.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I was one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:49:34.154 --> 00:49:36.323 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I knew that some people might be prejudiced

00:49:36.323 --> 00:49:39.026 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
against Witnesses, but I was surprised

00:49:39.026 --> 00:49:42.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to see how everyone could change so suddenly.

00:49:42.229 --> 00:49:45.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I started spending more time
with my classmates,

00:49:45.832 --> 00:49:48.135 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but the more I hung out with them,
the more I saw

00:49:48.135 --> 00:49:51.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we were living
completely different lives.

00:49:51.004 --> 00:49:54.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Their conversations would be
about trips they went on over the weekend

00:49:54.541 --> 00:49:56.610 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and what they bought
on their latest shopping trip, 

00:49:57.544 --> 00:50:00.814 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but when it came to me,
all I had done was spiritual activities.

00:50:00.814 --> 00:50:03.316 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It felt like I was missing out.

00:50:03.817 --> 00:50:07.387 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I felt alone and like an outcast.

00:50:07.387 --> 00:50:11.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I knew in my head that Bible principles
are right and beneficial,

00:50:11.758 --> 00:50:14.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but when I was
actually put in that situation,

00:50:14.561 --> 00:50:16.630 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wasn’t so sure anymore.

00:50:18.331 --> 00:50:22.502 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I started to feel like I wasn’t as cool
as my classmates,

00:50:22.502 --> 00:50:24.838 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so when they started to talk
about their life goals,

00:50:24.838 --> 00:50:28.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I couldn’t bring myself to tell them
what my goals were.

00:50:28.742 --> 00:50:31.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I started thinking,

00:50:31.311 --> 00:50:34.081 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘What would be the right way for me to act?’

00:50:34.681 --> 00:50:38.585 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Opening up to my parents
about my situation really helped.

00:50:38.585 --> 00:50:41.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One day for family worship, we decided

00:50:41.688 --> 00:50:44.024 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to discuss that topic.

00:50:44.024 --> 00:50:46.526 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We read Matthew 5:11:

00:50:46.526 --> 00:50:50.597 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Happy are you when people reproach you
and persecute you

00:50:50.597 --> 00:50:52.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and lyingly say every sort of wicked thing

00:50:52.699 --> 00:50:54.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
against you for my sake.”

00:50:55.368 --> 00:50:58.405 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But how can you be happy when persecuted?

00:50:59.039 --> 00:51:02.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I thought to myself,
‘But I’m not happy right now.’

00:51:02.242 --> 00:51:05.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My mom shared Mark 8:38 with me.

00:51:05.779 --> 00:51:07.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The part in the scripture where it says

00:51:07.380 --> 00:51:09.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that if we are ashamed of Jesus Christ,

00:51:09.382 --> 00:51:11.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he will be ashamed of us

00:51:11.418 --> 00:51:13.420 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
really hit me.

00:51:13.420 --> 00:51:15.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I realized that deep inside

00:51:15.722 --> 00:51:17.791 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I had been ashamed of being a Witness.

00:51:18.391 --> 00:51:19.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
While I was going through all of this,

00:51:19.926 --> 00:51:23.196 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a brother gave
a public talk in our congregation

00:51:23.196 --> 00:51:26.366 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and read Matthew 19:29.

00:51:26.366 --> 00:51:28.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There it says that everyone who has left

00:51:28.869 --> 00:51:31.805 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
what is important to them
“for the sake of [Jehovah]

00:51:31.805 --> 00:51:34.641 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will receive a hundred times as much.”

00:51:34.641 --> 00:51:39.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I decided to try leaving
what I thought was important to me

00:51:39.012 --> 00:51:42.315 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and seeing what results
and blessings I might receive.

00:51:42.315 --> 00:51:44.317 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
About that time,

00:51:44.317 --> 00:51:47.254 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
my parents helped me to associate
with brothers and sisters

00:51:47.254 --> 00:51:51.324 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who were participating
in many different forms of full-time service

00:51:51.324 --> 00:51:53.527 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so that I could hear their experiences.

00:51:53.527 --> 00:51:55.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That helped me to decide

00:51:55.996 --> 00:51:58.799 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
which direction I wanted to go in my life.

00:51:58.799 --> 00:52:02.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One thing that was really great
about this decision

00:52:02.068 --> 00:52:05.806 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was that I was able to meet
many new brothers and sisters.

00:52:05.806 --> 00:52:08.608 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I realized that there were so many people

00:52:08.608 --> 00:52:11.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who had the same thoughts and goals as I did.

00:52:11.511 --> 00:52:14.047 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These were my true friends.

00:52:14.047 --> 00:52:17.951 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The next time the topic of our future goals
came up with my classmates,

00:52:17.951 --> 00:52:20.220 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I was able to speak up confidently.

00:52:20.220 --> 00:52:22.489 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I am really thankful to my parents

00:52:22.489 --> 00:52:24.791 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who helped me to find the courage to do that.

00:52:24.791 --> 00:52:29.029 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve felt that Jehovah
truly keeps his promises.

00:52:29.029 --> 00:52:31.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come to think of it,

00:52:31.097 --> 00:52:33.733 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has kept his promise to reward me

00:52:33.733 --> 00:52:35.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a hundred times as much

00:52:35.869 --> 00:52:39.372 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
if I choose to live
by the Bible’s principles.

00:52:41.041 --> 00:52:43.210 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I am really happy now,

00:52:43.210 --> 00:52:47.914 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I am confident that if I follow
the Bible’s teachings when I make decisions,

00:52:47.914 --> 00:52:51.251 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I will always have the best results.

00:53:04.631 --> 00:53:07.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They were familiar with the Bible.

00:53:07.200 --> 00:53:10.103 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But its value became real to them

00:53:10.103 --> 00:53:13.506 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when they put Bible principles into practice.

00:53:15.775 --> 00:53:20.180 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This month’s program underscored
that in difficult times,

00:53:20.180 --> 00:53:22.616 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah always comforts.

00:53:23.717 --> 00:53:27.120 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Servants of Jehovah
like Sister Brown and her daughter

00:53:27.120 --> 00:53:29.956 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
may suffer terrible blows.

00:53:31.124 --> 00:53:34.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But no matter what happens to us,
even “if we die,

00:53:35.161 --> 00:53:38.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we [always] belong to Jehovah.”

00:53:38.365 --> 00:53:40.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Bible truths were a comfort to Maombi,

00:53:40.634 --> 00:53:44.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
 who never gave up searching for God.

00:53:44.437 --> 00:53:48.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And finally, all of us provide comfort

00:53:48.441 --> 00:53:50.911 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when we show impartial love.

00:53:52.045 --> 00:53:54.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now it’s time for our video postcard.

00:53:55.415 --> 00:53:58.818 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This month we visit our brothers in Alaska.

00:54:01.388 --> 00:54:05.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Alaska is in the far northwest corner
of North America.

00:54:06.126 --> 00:54:08.395 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One third of it lies
within the Arctic Circle.

00:54:08.395 --> 00:54:11.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In some areas, temperatures can drop

00:54:11.464 --> 00:54:14.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
below negative 60 degrees Fahrenheit,

00:54:14.367 --> 00:54:16.970 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or negative 54 degrees Celsius.

00:54:17.871 --> 00:54:21.408 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is a sparsely populated land
of glaciers,

00:54:21.408 --> 00:54:23.410 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
permafrost, and tundra

00:54:23.410 --> 00:54:25.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and is a rich habitat

00:54:25.178 --> 00:54:27.580 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for bears, caribou,

00:54:27.580 --> 00:54:31.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
moose, whales,
and dozens of species of fish.

00:54:31.985 --> 00:54:35.255 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s visit the Kuskokwim Congregation
in Bethel, Alaska.

00:54:36.056 --> 00:54:38.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s right
—the village is named Bethel!

00:54:38.758 --> 00:54:41.494 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Twenty-two publishers preach
in a territory that includes

00:54:41.494 --> 00:54:45.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
13 villages connected by waterways.

00:54:45.465 --> 00:54:48.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As the weather and seasons change,

00:54:48.001 --> 00:54:50.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so does their choice of transportation.

00:54:51.738 --> 00:54:53.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Four-wheelers and snowmobiles are common

00:54:53.740 --> 00:54:56.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
since many villages lack roads and cars.

00:54:57.577 --> 00:55:01.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This “road”
is actually on top of a frozen river.

00:55:01.815 --> 00:55:03.817 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s a caravan of publishers

00:55:03.817 --> 00:55:06.119 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on their way to the village of Kwethluk.

00:55:06.119 --> 00:55:10.590 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To be safe,
brothers travel with two or more vehicles

00:55:10.590 --> 00:55:13.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in case one gets stuck or breaks down.

00:55:13.493 --> 00:55:16.096 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Daily sunlight varies with the seasons

00:55:16.096 --> 00:55:18.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from less than 6 hours during winter

00:55:18.798 --> 00:55:22.268 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to more than 19 during summer.

00:55:22.268 --> 00:55:24.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The congregation includes

00:55:24.270 --> 00:55:28.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
nine regular and five special pioneers.

00:55:28.041 --> 00:55:30.877 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
An average of 85 Bible studies

00:55:30.877 --> 00:55:33.013 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are conducted every month.

00:55:33.013 --> 00:55:35.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In addition to an English congregation,

00:55:35.615 --> 00:55:37.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there is a Yupik pregroup.

00:55:38.451 --> 00:55:41.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Dog sledding
is an important part of Yupik culture.

00:55:41.788 --> 00:55:44.424 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Several races are held here every year.

00:55:45.191 --> 00:55:47.193 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This Bible student is wearing

00:55:47.193 --> 00:55:49.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a traditional garment called a qaspeq.

00:55:49.729 --> 00:55:53.833 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many at the meetings
give their comments in Yupik

00:55:53.833 --> 00:55:55.835 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and have them translated into English.

00:55:55.835 --> 00:55:59.139 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Although most publishers
aren’t fluent in Yupik,

00:55:59.139 --> 00:56:01.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they use publications and videos

00:56:01.174 --> 00:56:04.044 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
translated into Yupik
in the ministry.

00:56:04.044 --> 00:56:06.079 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Baptisms are normally held

00:56:06.079 --> 00:56:09.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at conventions and assemblies
in the city of Anchorage.

00:56:09.416 --> 00:56:12.485 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But this Bible student
made her dedication to Jehovah

00:56:12.485 --> 00:56:14.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
during the COVID-19 pandemic.

00:56:14.888 --> 00:56:17.257 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Despite the frigid weather,

00:56:17.257 --> 00:56:19.659 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
she was baptized in this river.

00:56:19.659 --> 00:56:21.661 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is where she grew up.

00:56:21.661 --> 00:56:24.697 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our brothers and sisters
from the Kuskokwim Congregation

00:56:24.697 --> 00:56:26.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Bethel, Alaska

00:56:26.699 --> 00:56:28.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
send their love and greetings

00:56:28.701 --> 00:56:30.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the worldwide brotherhood!

00:56:31.805 --> 00:56:34.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:56:34.974 --> 00:56:37.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

